\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Could I have your name, present address and marital status?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Daniel. Daniel Goodchild.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 89 Taybridge Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And your marital status, have you been married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, I was - I have been married. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What was your year of marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 1928. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And your year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 1897.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And your birthplace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Shoreditch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh - that I can't tell you. I mean I was - I was too young to remember. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Where did you go to from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 From - my first - abode, I went to a - an orphanage. Yes. In - at Homerton. Sidney Road. Homerton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Could you tell me why you went into an orphanage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well I - really - my mother, she had ten children. And - every other one died. I was the last one to live. Livin
g two girls and three boys. Well - the two girls, they were adopted. By a - foster parents but we three boys, the eldest boy went to Enfield Schools and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was that an orphanage?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, that was a Poor Law school. Yes. And - my second brother and I we went to - Sidney Road, Homerton - cottages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So you had your brother with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 My second brother with me, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Could you tell me the birth order of your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well I - really I suppose they averaged two years between each. About two years between each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What order did they come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well that - well I don't know quite the order but - they left - they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7891465\charrsid7304980 left}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  two girls and three boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were the girls older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes. Yes, both girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How about the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
The - the - the - eldest boy was - the third. He was the third in the family and then Harry, the second one, I followed Harry. I was the youngest of the lot, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Have you any idea how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well no, I've no idea - no idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 When did he die?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 I don't know that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Or his age when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No. I don't know anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Do you know where he came from originally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, I know his - he was Londoner. He was a Londoner, yes, they were both Londoners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 He was a walking stick maker. Yes. Yes, yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Do you know if he ever had any job before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And you don't know how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Or whether she had an occupation before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, I've no idea, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How many orphanages were you in, how long were you in this one at Homerton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - at Homerton I was - I suppose I was about twelve m
onths. And in that time I was - I caught ring-worms and went into the infirmary for a few weeks. Well, twice this occurred and the second time I definitely remember having them burnt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How old would you be then, this would be one your earliest memories then would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Yes, yes. I suppose I was about three. About three then. Only I - I - well remember it. This may sound a - a wee bit funny but - while I was in the infirmary, being the only one that could run about the ward naturally the maid got me 
to - empty their bottles for them. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 And - I'd been doing rather well at this, a ha'penny a time and - but one day I got a bit too energetic and slipped, broke a bottle and cut me hand badly. }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So of course the nurse stopped me doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 This is why you remember- this so clearly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes. That's right, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How old were you then when you left this infirmary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 When I - when I left the - when I left Homerton I went to Brentwood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 At what age was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh - about five I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How long did you stay in Brentwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Oh - I went there, I went straight into the infants, what they called the infants and then - when I became - seven years of age I went to the big boys. Still in Brentwood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Under the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7891465\charrsid7304980 same}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  roof?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Un
der the same - yes, there was a - it was a big school about six - about - three or four hundred boys and three or four hundred girls. Yes. Oh yes, yes. Very. And I joined the big boys when I was seven years of age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And how long did you stay with the big boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh - stayed there - let's see - six years. Round about six years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You'd be between thirteen and fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Fourteenish or fifteen I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 think}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  it was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And that was the end of your time in the orphanage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no, no, no, it wasn't the end of me time. I went from Brentwood to Ongar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 At fifteen you went from Brentwood to Ongar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Yes. Yes. And - the school, it was slightly different, we were in cottages there, you see, Brentwood was a barrack school but Ongar was a co
ttage school and - cottages they said but there was fifty boys in each cottage, so it was some cottage. Yes, yes, yes. Yes, I've been there once since I left, yes, yes. Oh yes. And then - I - Brentwood, I left - Brentwood - I mean I left Ongar and joined 
the Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What age was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Fifteen and a half. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You went in the Army at fifteen and a half?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 The infants section, how was this laid out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well this - yes, no, no, the infants section was away from the
 main building you see, the main building was the school. The infants section was more over the hospital way and there was - between thirty and forty little ones over there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were there any other people in the houses besides children, did you have house fathers sleep in them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well - no. Well at - at Brentwood we had - we had - five men attendants that used to - govern the boys. The ladies - the girls had the same over their side you see. And - well - when you'd been there a little while you got th
e option of learning a trade. You could - there was - carpenters, plumbers, shoemakers, tailors, painters, engineers, bakers, even farming. Oh yes, yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you have any slight task to carry out, what you might call household task, like 
laying tables or cleaning rooms or running errands of any sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Not - not at Brentwood. But at Ongar, yes. You see, as - as it was a big cottage - fifty boys in there, we had our own dining room and the elder boys used to have to lay the tables and do all the cleaning, scrubbing and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So it became self contained like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Up until that time you were more or less looked after by domestic staff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - the only - the only things we used to have to do was - make
 our own beds and keep the dormitories clean. And polish the floors etcetera.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was there any sort of family atmosphere in the place, did you help the younger boys get dressed or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Not - no, not at - not at Brentwood. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You more or less had to fend for yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
That's right, yes. You see, and of course the - the school itself was - we had our own squads, that small - young boys up to the - elder boys and we had six different squads, sizes and ages you see. And of cou
rse when - when the whistle blew everybody stopped. Number one squad to bed. And so on. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You had different bedtimes according to age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 We had different dormitories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Can you remember the bedtimes from the beginning when you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Oh the - the younger boys used to go to bed - oh - about sevenish. Yes. Yes. And the boys - older boys used to go - perhaps eight - half past in the summer you see. That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 The dormitory? Oh no, there was about twenty to thirty beds in - in the dormitories Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 those}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
 single or bunk beds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Singles, single - single beds, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What sort of place was the bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh we had a - we had a - we had a huge bathroom with sprays and - wash bowls and everything like that. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Once a week we used to have to have a bath. Yes. Once a week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes, clean clothes. Clean underclothes but - your ordinary clothes we used to have to keep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What sort of clothes did you have, was it a uniform?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, well part uniform. Sort of - a Norfolk jacket and - knickers, you see, with stockings and boots. Yes, yes, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Where did you have the meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Oh we had the meals in a large dining hall. The dining hall - used to separate the boys from the girls. In the centre you see. And - well we were - when the whistle blew we fell in and we were marched into our special tables, always had t
he same tables you see, although not the same place. And of course - we take our position in the hall, in the dining hall, and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  used to come in and - one of the officers used to play grace, we used to sing grace, you see, and then we'd sit down. Well one of the - strictest things this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 
superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  used to insist on was - everybody used to have to chew each mouthful thirty times. Yes, and he used to watch you. And - if you didn't you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you have to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well - they - they - they - yes, they taught you that sort of thing. Yes, that's right, yes, yes. They taught you that. And they taught you to keep your mouth closed while you were chewing. Oh yes, that - all those sort of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - no. Oh no. You were allocated so much and that was it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Could you ask people to pass things like the salt or did you have to wait until it was offered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well there were - there were cruets 
on - on the table, the salt and peppers. And - that's right, you passed them along. Yes, oh yes. That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Who served the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well, the meals came from the kitchen. From the kitchen and there were maids that used to bring them along. 
On big trolleys, yes. Already on the plates on the trollies and we used to pass them up the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So you just took the plate off with the food already on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, already on, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was there any special order that you were served in or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No. Oh no. No talking. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 If you didn't like some food were you allowed to leave it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - they wanted to know what was strong with it if you left it. And if your answer wasn't - suitable well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 It wasn't nough to just say, I don't like greens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
No, they - they would tell you that they - that would do you good, greens do you good. And you'd have to do your best to get it down. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were you allowed to take books or toys or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 have}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  anything with you at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no, not at the table. No, no. We had a large day room for that sort of thing you see. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did the school - you said you could learn farming and things like this - did they grow any of their own fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Yes, oh yes. Grew a lot of their own vegetables, they kept - kept their own milk, their own eggs. And their own pigs. Yes. It was a huge farm, about thirty cows. Yes. And they had - four horses - that used t
o take the school brake. You see, they had a huge brake that - say the band - you see, say the band was going out to an engagement, all the band would pile onto this brake, see, and away to -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Like the school bus?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, yes, that's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did all the boys do a certain }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 amount}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  of work on the farm or was this just the boys learning farming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - what used to happen was - when you got a certain age and you got to a certain standard, say standard six as we used to call it, th
en you - no, standard five - then you used to go part time - half time. What you used to do was you'd go to school in the morning and you'd go to your train - your training in the afternoon, whatever your shop was. Tailor, shoemaker, carpenter or whatever
 it was or farm you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And at what age is this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
That used to start - that used to start - round about thirteen or fourteen. Then when you got - then you went full time on - on the job, yes, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Most children pick up their ideas from their parents don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you have a particular housefather or someone in charge of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
We had - what we had - we used to call him Drilly. He was the drill master and he was the head of the - men attendants, you see, and of course, what he said go - went. And the others - well, just used to keep control of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Like an ordinary schoolmaster would more or less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes - that's right. We had our own school - we had our own teachers. In the school - in the classrooms and that
. We had our own teachers, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 If you had any personal worries or difficulties who would you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - well - we could go to the drill master. That's right, and if he couldn't deal with it he used to take you to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  do any teaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no, he was just the head of the whole concern. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
In orphanages they have a group of eight or ten and you have one man you treat almost like a father inasmuch as you go to him with all your troubles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Oh yes, well that happened when we moved to Ongar. You see, we was at the cottages again you see. And of course we had foster parents there. We had a mother and father and a maid. And each cottage - our cottage - my particular cottage was the 
band master. And we had the band there you see. The next one was the carpenter. The next one was the plumber, and the gardener and so on you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 But you're already fourteen at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you feel that the staff were easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes. You could always go and speak to them. That's right, yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 
Very, very friendly. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 There was only one - well, they were very strict mind you, very strict. Even having a bath - you used to have to queue up and you were inspected to see 
that you'd washed behind your ears. And if you hadn't you got a sting across the bottom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 But you thought they were quite affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Quite - quite normal you know. You could go and speak to them and that. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How did they bring you up to treat the rest of the boys, would you say you treated them like brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well - yes, yes, yes, we all used - all used to play games together and all the rest of it you see. There's one very particular thing about that thou
gh. Very peculiar I always used to think. Now there was several sets of brothers. Same as my brother and I - several sets. Now - you take about three hundred boys playing in a playground, all shouting, screaming at the top of their voices. And yet - one b
oy could call out - my skissle. And his brother would know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What's my skissle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 My brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What sort of slang is that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Just a word we heard - among ourselves. My skissle. Yes. And it don't matter - it didn't matter which pair of brothe
rs it was the brother used to know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And you and your brother used to stick together a bit?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right - oh yes, oh yes, brothers were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You had the usual childhood scraps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, oh yes. Yes. Oh yes, we used to play games, robbers and things you know and sometimes - used to get hurt pretty bad. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 We had a giant stride in the playground, the boys\rquote  playground, and it was right - it was about six yards away from the wall that separated the boys\rquote  toilets, you see. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well what we used
 to like to do on this giant stride was get our rope, it had about eight ropes on it, you see, tied from a long pole - eight ropes and you used to hold these ropes and all swing round and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Like a Maypole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, like a Maypole only you -
 you used to swing yourself up. What we used to like to do was to get our rope over the boy behind so that as he pulled it chick us right high. Well one day one of the boys thought it was a bit clever and he got too high and he slipped - his hand slipped 
and he sailed over this wall right into the boys toilets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They wouldn't permit swearing or anything would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no, we never used to know what swearing was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You never heard it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, no, never heard that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 If }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 two}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
 or three of the teachers were talking were you allowed to go and butt in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well no, you - if they were talking together you just went and stood - at respectable distance and - waited 'til you caught their eye. Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 If you did something they disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well, I'll tell you one instance. What happened in a class room one day. There was one - we had a new teacher and we didn't particularly like him. I think I was in standard four at the time and - one of the boys, as this t
eacher was going past him, you see he used to always keep his handkerchief in his outside pocket - pocket you see. This boy, as he went by, he tipped his inkwell into the pocket and of course when the teacher went to wipe his nose he was all ink. Oh - we 
all had the cane for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were people punished very often do you think?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, not very often. It had to be - something - fairly severe. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How did they keep control without punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - if - if the - if the - attendants - wanted to punish you - really they used to take you to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  and he'd give you the cane, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 But normally it would be like a tongue dressing would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did they give you lines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, no, we never used to have lines. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 It was more or less their own personality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
That's right, yes. Their own personality. When you were in the classrooms at school then the teachers used to deal with you there. And when the - when you were out - outside the schoolrooms the other staff used to - take you to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 . Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Do you remember how you felt about being punished, can you remember any incident of being punished yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes, I can remember - I remember once - I forget what i
t was I done, I know I - I think I answered a teacher back. And - I had to touch me toes. And unfortunately for me I had a hole in me trousers. And the teacher was real - a dead eye with the cane and he caught this patch every time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How many strokes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Six. Six, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 This was with a normal cane was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How did you feel about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well naturally we used to sort of - rebel against it but it wasn't much good rebelling much or else you only made it worse for yourself.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Do you feel you were unjustly punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, no, I would never say that. No. If a boy was punished he deserved it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 He'd usually gone far enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes. That's right, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Where would you say you received your ideas on how to behave, would you say one person was more important than the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well naturally we used to take a leaf out of the older boys books. The older boys, yes, oh yes, they set the - they set the example.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Rather more than the ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 The smaller boys, that's - that's why it was that the elder boys always used to be - any - anything wrong they used to carry the can back.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So as you got older you had quite a lot of responsibility?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes. Oh yes, yes, we sort of made }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7891465\charrsid7304980 prefects,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  as you got older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 People tend to imitate their parents, if their parents are generous friendly sort of people they tend to think that's a good thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Where do you think you got your standards from, just the place as a whole rather than any individual would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well I - on the whole I think, the place as a whole because we - we never had - except at Ongar. And of course - well - they were on a par with the - the - the teachers at Brentwood really, we had to do as we were told.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So you would say it was your environment as a whole rather than single individuals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, yes, oh yes, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 If you had a birthday did they make anything of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No. No. There was no special - no special - things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You didn't have a present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Or anything special to eat?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, no. The only time we used to get presents was at Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Could you tell me about Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, yes, yes. It was - we k
new it wasn't - we knew it wasn't much good banging our stocking up because - but we used to look forward to the Christmas dinner. Then in the afternoon we used to go to the - big hall and there was entertainments. Then after the entertainment we used to 
have the - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7296982\charrsid7304980 Christmas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  tea. And after Christmas tea we used to play games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What sort of games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well - sheep - sheep come home and - yes, well we - we - all the boys were the sheep you see, and the - the officers were the wolves. And you used to
 have to try and get through them without being caught. And if you were caught you were out. And it was the last boy that was left - what used to get the prize.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What did you have for breakfast as a rule?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well usually - bread and butter. Bread - two slices of bread and butter. And a cup of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What time would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh - should be about eight o'clock. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you never have porridge or egg and bacon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes - not egg and bacon. Now and again we'd have porridge. Instead of bread and butter, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And jam or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 marmalade}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2182234\charrsid7304980 That\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  for tea time. That's tea time, jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So breakfast would either be bread and butter on its own or porridge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2182234\charrsid7304980 That\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
