e away from the school and then we turn into this Honeypot Lane and of course then - then we used to start - we were allowed to break off - break out of line and - go and find what we could in the hedges and bring it to the master to - to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Like a nature ramble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, like a nature walk, that's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And do a bit of bird nestin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2182234\charrsid7304980 g mice}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  or something like that. That's right, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 On Bank Holidays would you ever be taken out somewhere, say to Clacton or somewhere, did you ever have any days like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 At Brentwood we had one day a year. We went to Southend - by train. And it was a thrill of a lifetime. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did they give you any money to spend on these outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - no. No. We had - we had sixpence each at Christmas. At Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was this your only pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That was the only pocket money that we used to get. Unless of course anybody's parents or friends gave them money when. - on visiting days.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You'd be unlucky in this respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes. Yes. And - and towards the end, at Ongar you see, my two sisters - they - they used to come and see me there. But not at Brentwood.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were they married by then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes. They were both married by them because they used to come down to Ongar to see me and - and they used to leave me with sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So you were about fourteen before you had pocket money really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes. Yes. Oh yes, yes. Yes. Well you didn't really need pocket money. We had our board lodgings and everything else. Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you ever feel envious when you saw the other town boys going into a sweet shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well no, we never - we - we were never jealous of them because we - we didn't know any different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You didn't have any contact with the local boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 We used to speak to some of them if - you know, if they spoke to us. But - we - we never knew any different you see. Bought up like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you feel that there was any animosity on behalf of the local boys to the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, the only animosity would - we used to get was when we played them at football. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 If we played the outside - an outside boys' team at football, then we used to have some animosity. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
But we played a boys - we played another school at Ongar and - well it was a - ever such a small pitch and naturally every time you kicked the ball you scored a goal. And we beat 'em thirteen none.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 But this was just the normal sporting animosity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, yes, yes. Oh nothing else, oh no. Oh no, no, no. Yes. Well we - once we went to - just outside On
gar we went to Fyfield where there was a Borstal school. And the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was this playing sport again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Sport. No, just tug-of-war. And - we beat them. Yes. Oh we used to have our own football team and cricket team and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You had a pretty full sporting programme?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you attend a place of worship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 We used to - our own - we used to go to our own hall. Our main hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You didn't go out to a church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Not at Brentwood. But at Ongar now and again we used to go down the beach to the church there. Of a Sunday evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Which denomination?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Church of England. Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were they very strict on religion, did they think it wrong to play or work on Sunday at the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes, you weren't allowed. Well you could - play in the playground, yes, play but - nothing - organised. No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You wouldn't be allowed to pick two teams for football for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, no. No. Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 But you could kick a ball around the playground?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You could kick a ball around. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How often did you have to attend the hall for worship on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Only - only just the - once. Yes. Yes. Used to have the clergyman from the village come in and - school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were there any activiti
es connected with church or with religion that weren't connected with the school, did they have a choir for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, we never had a choir. But - what we - what we used to do - at Ongar was - there was a little church just outside Ongar called Sh
erry and we used to go there, see, some Sundays. Well, the band master took the band there on a Harvest Festival and - we played the - took the service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 But if you went to the church it would always be with a supervisor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's - oh yes, oh yes. Oh yes, you didn't go out unless you were under supervision.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They were quite strict on that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh very strict. Oh yes. Very strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you ever try to play }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2182234\charrsid7304980 hookey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  at all and sneak out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - now and again - now and again we used to get a boy used to do it but he always used to come back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 I meant perhaps sneak out for a couple of hours in the evening without telling anyone
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no. No, you couldn't get away with that, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 There was nothing like temperance clubs or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No. No. Oh no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you have to say grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, we used to sing grace. Before and after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, we used to - we used to say }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7891465\charrsid7304980 prayers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  in the - we used to assemble in the day room see, and the - supervisor in charge used to - we used to say our prayer then. And off straight to bed. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were you aware of any political activities while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Never dreamt of it. No, never dreamt of it. Never heard the staff talk about it or anything. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 When did you interest yourself in politics, when did you become aware of politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Politics - when I left the Army. Not 'til - the Army'd got no time for politics. No. You don't hear a
ny arguments or anything like that in the Army about politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How old would you have been when you left the Army then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 I left the Army when I was twenty-seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So you were very late coming round to politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Politics - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you have any political interests after you left the Army?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - yes. Yes. I always used to - I was always blue. I was blue. Still are. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were you at all aware of the staff as having a life of their own as it were outside the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 W
ell, yes, we used to know that - some of the - at Brentwood you see some of the staff used to live out in the town. There were, you know, two or three of them used to live in, they had their own little rooms at the end of the dormitories. But - some used 
to come in regular every day and go home at night. Yes, well that - we never used to know anything of their private lives. No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you feel that the world was -?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 The world was outside. That's right, yes. Yes, oh yes, we knew, that's why we
 - we were always bursting to get out. We wanted to see - a little bit of world. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You felt there was something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, yes, and of course if we went out in - out to the town and we saw the shops, walked right through the town, the Hig
h Street you see and we used to love to get up onto - Shenfield Common. And then we'd have a - a break. Have a ramble round and when the whistle blew we'd all fall in again and - back we'd go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were you ever taken shopping at all at the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, no. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 The clothes were took to you more or less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Oh no, the clothes - clothes - shoes, clothes, all made in the school. Yes. By the boys, yes. I used to go to the band you see and also go to the shoemaker. So I - I - well I used to make me own shoes and dozens of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2182234\charrsid7304980 other}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  pairs of shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Completely made, just not repaired?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Complete - no, not only repairs, the shoes, right from the uppers to the - the - the shoemaker used to cut out by machine, you see, cut out the uppers, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 send}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  those away to be s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
wn up. When they came back we used to have to assemble them. And he used to cut out the soles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Sewing on the uppers was done outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes. Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 But you had to attach the upper to the sole?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, yes. 'Cos we had a - we had a wonderful }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 shoe shop}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 . Wonderful shoe - we used to make all the staffs' - shoes as well. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You also made all the clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes. We - we used to make all the boys clothes in the - in the tailors shop you see. And the
 girls had their own - place to make the girls clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What about shirts and underclothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well they used to make - the girls department. That's right yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How about socks and knitted things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - no, you they used to buy those. An
d we used to have to darn them. We used to have to darn our own socks, if you made holes in your socks you used to have to darn them. And darn them properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How often did you have new ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well what used to happen was - your - your socks, if t
hey got too bad, they were passed on to another boy, you see, as he became older so he took over your socks. But it was remarkable you know - I always used to suffer with my feet - perspiring and when our - when our stockings - stockings we had - when our
 stockings came back from the laundry, I had no trouble in finding mine. I used to feel for the feet. And if they were stiff I knew they were mine. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was there anyone you felt particularly close to at this stage, you say you got on well with your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Oh yes, we always used to have our - special pals. I had a - a fellow named Withers - Denny Willis we used to call him. He came a - he became a band master when he left and joined the Army. Oh yes, we had our special - and it used to be - you 
usually used to find that - bandsmen would clique together you see and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 According to interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 The same with the shops, carpenters and all that, had their own little clique.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you ever play with children outside the place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, we u
sed to all play together at Brentwood. But at Ongar at the cottages, each cottage had their own bit of playground you see and you - you kept to that. Except sometimes at night when it got dark we used to wander around and - if we felt particular hungry - 
we used to what we called laugh up. Laugh up. Then we used to go to the larder of two cottages away you see, open the window and see what we could get.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You didn't steal from your own larder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no, we didn't steal from our own larder, oh no. How
 that came about - well as - there was something missing one day and the band master punished us. And he turned round and he said, huh, now this is where the small boys laugh up their sleeves, see, at the big boys. So of course when we got out we say all 
right, well - we'll go and see what we can find. We went. And when we came back we said, now this is where the big boys laugh up their sleeves. Laugh up. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What games did you play, you told me you played football and cricket, were there any other sports you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Among ourselves. Oh well, we used to - all sorts of - all sorts of games that - boys usually play. You know - cigarettes against the wall. And - we used to - we used to do flick'ums. That's also with cigarette cards. You fix a cigare
tte in that joint there and you - go like that and it goes quite a long way. See, the; }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 furthest}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  one - yes, yes, the }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 furthest}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  one picks 'em up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well if you got dirty you simply get yourself clean again. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 
Before you sat down to meals anyway, 'cos - very often they'd file us into the day room and - inspect your hands before you went into the dining room.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What about if you scuffed }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2182234\charrsid7304980 your}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  shoes playing football or got your clothes mucky?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Before you went to bed at night you had to clean your shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 This was every night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Every night, you paraded in front of the - foster parent with your shoes. And if they weren't clean back you went to the - used to have a special little cubby hole where we used to keep all the shoe stuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What happened if you were playing about and you got your jacket ripped or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well then of course you used to have to take it - your foster parents 'd send you to the tailors shop to have it mended.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They didn't punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no. Oh no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They were pretty understanding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, oh yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 They used to allow for the boys' spirits did they?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, the boys sprits. We - at Ongar you know we had a - a wonderf
ul big oval - grass oval in the centre of the school in between the boys and girls, and all round the edge of the oval were apple trees. They were only young apple trees in those days but they used to bear fruit. And the consequence was that - we used to 
fancy some of this fruit at times. So what used to happen at night time, we used to wait and watch the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 night watchman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
, wait 'til he'd gone a certain distance away then we used to get out the window, onto the fire escape, down the fire escape, see, a couple 
of us, run to these trees, one used to shake the tree while the other one held out his night shirt to catch the apples. Take 'em back to the dormitory and eat }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2182234\charrsid7304980 them.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  Well that was - well it was all right until one day there was about six of us - taken }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 with diarrhea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 . And of course they rumbled what it was. They'd taken them to green that's what it was. Boys can never wait you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You said after you got to Ongar your sisters used to visit you, were they allowed to take you out without these supervisors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No. No. 'h no. No. No, they used to all - in certain part we used to - meet the visitors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 In a room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well outside. There was a sort of miniature playground, see. And chairs and tables outside there. And of course - in the winter - in the 
winter - visiting day was once a month. Once a month - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How long did a visit last?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 About two hours. Yes, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were you allowed pets or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well, yes, we were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2182234\charrsid7304980 because}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  my pal and I, we kept a rabbit. Yes. We kept rabbits. And - some boys had pigeons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 These weren't part of the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no, no. This was at Ongar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How about at Brentwood?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no, we never had anything, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How about toys or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, what we used to - what we u
sed to - we used to have a - a locker. See, two of you used to have to share a locker. And you used to keep - keep all your rubbish in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You could keep more or less what you liked in there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What you liked in there, within reason. As long as it didn't start smelling or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 After you went to Ongar you were allowed a bit more freedom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You'd keep rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were you allowed to keep dogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No. Yes, nobody had a dog. Oh yes, we weren't allowed any dogs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 But you could have caged animals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, that's all I think, yes. If you could afford it that is. Afford it, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You said you went for walks, did you ever go out to do other things like fishing, or did you have bicycles, did you go cycling at all?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, no, no. No, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How about theatres or concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - at Brent wood I remember going to - the Mikado. Out in the Town Hall once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 This was a pantomime was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, it's a play, the Mikado it's called. Gilbert and Sullivan, yes, I remember seeing that. But that's the only time I ever saw any -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They didn't take you to the cinema?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You never went to the cinema while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Never knew what the cinema was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You didn't go to the cinema until after you joined the Army then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And certainly not music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh - no, no,. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You say your pocket }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2182234\charrsid7304980 money}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  was sixpence once a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Once a year,
 yes. Well what - one Christmas at Ongar the band went out playing carols, and we used to go to a - a big mansion about five miles outside Ongar - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 McCorquodale's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 . And we used to play the carols out on their front lawn. And then all the guests you see used 
to come out, and - Mr McCorquodale used to come out, he'd give the bandmaster five pounds. Imagine how we felt. Five pounds. Fantastic. Well of course he handed it in when we got back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you get sixpence or a shilling out of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well they gave
 us a - a tea and buns at the mansion you see, they gave us tea and buns but - we were glad to get that, quite content too. Quite content, yes, oh yes. Oh yes. Oh we ploughed through the snow you know, we didn't mind. No, you see we used to think anything
 like that was marvellous. Wonderful. Just to get out, that's right, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What did you spend your sixpence on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - what we used to do - we used to wait until - we got down in the village you see and then - usually they used to let us have
 a break of five minutes and there was a little tuck shop that we used to go and we used to have say a penn'orth of brandy balls, sixteen a penny. We'd have a penn'orth of cherry bonkers. They are toffees. And then we used to have a - a slab of Japanese t
offee. Another penny. What else would it be - we used to have - oh sherbert draws, four sherbert draws a penny. Oh - four - four strips of licorice, another penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 It was all sweets then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 All sweets - all sweets, nothing else was any good. We tho
ught we - once we saw some locusts in - the window and we thought we'd try them. But we - but we didn't do it a second time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Are these the locust beans?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, locust, the insect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Your sisters came to visit you when you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 got}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  to Ongar, were they living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no, they - Ongar's about twenty-five miles from London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They settled in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They settled in London. One settled at Homerton, Dalby Road Homerton, the other one went to Kentish Town. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did they come down every month?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Oh no, they couldn't afford to come down every month. Oh no. And sometimes they'd come - I didn't know they were coming, you see. 'Cos they - well writing letters and all that used to take twice as long. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So you didn't have much contact with your relatives at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
No, no. No, no. Oh no. No, the same thing applies to me eldest brother you see, he was in a different school. He went and joined the Marines. And - then - me second brother joined the Essex Regiment and I went and joined the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 Bedford\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And you lost contact with them did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were you allowed to invite friends into the home, any other boys you'd met in the town or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No. Oh no. No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were you aware before 1918 of different social classes or groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Not in the school. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You felt they were all much about the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, well of course in the - in - in the Army, when I first joined the Army, yes, you could realise i
t then. Because of - well, because of the officers you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What sort of groups would you s-lit society into before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well when - when there was a - a sports or anything - a regimental sports or anything like that you see, all the officers 
friends used to come and of course the sergeants and each others friends used to come but they never mixed. No. No, no. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were they separate again from the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 N.C.Os}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - well the - the N.C.O's - the sergeants and sergeant majors used to 
sort of drift apart from the - rest of them. The corporals and the privates - yes, they - they'd mix. But it was - there was - the same difference -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You weren't aware of this sort of division in industry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You would have been isolated from this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well of course you see - being in the Army when the - the war broke out and in the Army still after the war well you never knew what - what was happening. No, no. We didn't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 While you were at the school were you brou
ght up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another sort, were you ever told to touch your cap or show respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes, anybody that we knew. Any body that we knew - we always used to show respect. Touch our caps to them. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You didn't have occasion to do this with people outside the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
If - if there was any - say the doctor. Say the doctor came. Well naturally if we met him out in the town we used to - touch our cap to him. Or - or the clergy - man who came you see, touch our cap. Anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were you taught to call anyone sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh of course it was always - always sir. Yes sir. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Who were considered the most important people in the district that you came in contact with, 
you said you had to touch your cap to the clergy and the doctor, how about farmers - you wouldn't come in contact with these people would you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 It was more or less just the people within your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 There was one farmer we
 used to touch our cap to. Yes, that was Farmer Pratt. Well his - his farm - his fields used to join the school, over the fence. And sometimes we used to get caught over the fence you see, and we got to know Farmer Pratt, so we used to touch our cap.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What class would you say Farmer Pratt was in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Oh he was quite a jovial - quite a jovial old chap mind you but - oh we used to - if he caught anybody then we used to go - we were up in front of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What level of society would you put him in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well middle-ish. Middle class. Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How about the doctor and clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Same, yes, middle class, yes. Oh yes. I mean we knew perfectly well that they were a different class to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 McCorquodale\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  that we used to go and play to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What were the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 McCorquodale\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well I told you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What class were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They were the - wealthy. Society. Yes, yes. Beautiful big mansion. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What class would you put your teachers in then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 I should think middle. Middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Would you make a distinction between them and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 superintendent}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  who didn't teach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - they were really - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  was above them - in station. In school station. But - I - I - still middle. Still middle - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How about the cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well, of course, the cook was one of the - lower staff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You didn't have any dealings with her at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No. No, no. Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - we 
had - a lady - I don't know - I don't remember the name but we had a Lady somebody come to the school once. And of course she was given the real - red carpet treatment. The V.I.P. But I forget the name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You'd say she was a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes. Yes. Y
es. I had a - I had a narrow escape of being adopted by a rich man. Narrow escape, I say. Well it was my own fault really because - this - gentleman who owned a sweet factory, he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2182234\charrsid7304980 wanted}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  to - to adopt a boy. And - came along to the school and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  said to about half a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2182234\charrsid7304980 dozen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
 of us, and this fellow picked out two of us and questioned us and all this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 than}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
- and the other and - be asked us if we'd like to become - his adopted son. Well - then I was so full of the Army, that my brothers were in the Army, I didn't want to be any gentleman's son you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh - fourteen and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's quite late for an adoption isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you lose many of the boys by adoption?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes, quite a few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 It's a kind of regular process?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 It is, it's a regular thing. They used to send them to Australia too and Canada. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 Emigration. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Would this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2182234\charrsid7304980 be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
 when they were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - in - any age - towards the growing up - yes - standard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 From about eleven onwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes. That's right, yes, they had the option of going to Australia or Canada.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 It's a young age to choose isn't it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 But - but there used to be dozens of them to go you know. Dozens of them used to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was this going to Canada to another orphanage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No. To an adopted parent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Who you hadn't seen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You hadn't seen, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They used to write from Canada or Australia and adopt them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, that's right, yes, yes. And I
 had a pal that went to Canada and he was out there a few weeks and he - he sent me a golden half sovereign. Yes, tucked in a piece of cardboard you know, a hole made and it fitted in and that - came - came through marvellous. I was a millionaire for - ab
out two years. Yes, he was - he was one of the lucky ones, he got in with a lovely family out in Canada.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 This }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7891465\charrsid7304980 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
 just a blind date as you might say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's it, yes, yes. Yes. Oh yes. Yes, and we had a - I remember one of the - one of the maids a
t the hospital, she went to Australia. She got married. Yes, and - and the girls - the girls used to go and the boys used to go. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you ever feel there was any pressure on you to put up for adoption or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, no. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How would they set about this, how would it happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well - they just - come to you and talk to you about - would you like to go to Australia? Well - naturally - the - the boys and girls, they'd go anywhere to get out of the school you see. That's how it used to come about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You never felt they were .....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Forcing you, oh no. No, they gave you the option. Oh definitely, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you have any dealings with policemen while you were at the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No. No, no. We knew what they were but we - we didn't have anything to do with them. No. No. Oh no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Do you think it was possible for people to move from one class to another before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well I think so really. It's all according to their - sort of - dispositions and
 - really, I mean - the majority - take - dance band boys. Majority of them were - typical Londoners, yet they cold move among the society. Oh yes, we often used to have to rub shoulders with the - the elite. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Do you know of anyone who moved up in society themselves rather than just mixed with them? How difficult do you think that would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes, well - you take some of the band leaders. They done it. Yes, you see. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So you wouldn't think class divisions were too solid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no. No, no, no, I think they were rather flexible. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 I want to know talk about your school, the school lessons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 The teaching part? Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What did the teachers emphasise as being important in life, do you think they emphasised 
anything in particular, like manners or ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well - we used to - we used to have a little of each. Oh yes. But the main lessons were reading, writing and arithmetic. And of course history and geography.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You had a good all round .....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How about things like tidiness or punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh most disciplined. Yes. They're quite - very - yes, oh yes, they were very strict. Very strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 If you did something they disapproved of what would happen to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well it - all according to the - the crime. The punishment to fit the crime. Some of the punishment was very severe. Others was just - bread and water or something. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Not literally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 A poor law school. It was a poor law school. In other words you see the - it was the - sub - workhouse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What did you think of the school side, the teaching side, did you enjoy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes. Oh yes, we used to quite enjoy that. We used to have three examinat
ions a year. Yes. And we had ten subjects. On each examination. Ten marks for each. So - and fortunately I used to manage to scrape out top. Yes, yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 In music as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 In the school were the girls still }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2182234\charrsid7304980 separate}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Yes, yes. In the school itself - in the school itself, well - at Brentwood - that was a barrack - like a barrack school. Well we were separate. But at Ongar we only had the one - school for the two and of course all the classes were mixed. Mixed classes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That was from fourteen onwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no, before that. That was before, that was - oh - about 1910. Somewhere round there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You would have been about thirteen years old would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Less than that when that - when I went to Ongar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were the girls punished the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - not exactly but they had their own headmistress that used to see to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did they get the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No. They were given something else. We never saw the girls punished. No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did they have lines or have to stay in, do you remember what they got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 I think it was more lines than anything. Yes. Yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 house parents}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  show any interest in your schoolwork, how you were progressing in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh they were two separate - two }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2182234\charrsid7304980 separate}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  things altogether, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 When I joined the Army? Well I was fifteen and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Would you have stayed at school longer if you had had the chance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No. I was dying - I was dying to get out of it. Dying to get out of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Do you think it would have been any different if you had been going to a school where you didn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2182234\charrsid7304980 live?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  A normal school, would you have been interested to have gone on then do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Probably, yes. Yes. But being in a - well we - you felt hemmed in, that you weren't allowed to - do this and do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 This was too powerful?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, yes. Although - when I left the school I carried on schooling i
n the Army. Oh yes. You had to. You see, directly I enlisted I went in - went to school and I got what was called the third - third certificate. Then I carried on and I got the second certificate, see. But I wasn't clever enough to get the first certifica
te. But if I hadn't have got the third certificate then I wouldn't have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 got}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  proficiency pay. See.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were these in general subjects or in Army subjects?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 More Army stuff than general.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Could you just say roughly what they consisted of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 Well - Army quotations - different - I used to use a lot of Army - what we never, never heard of it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Echelon and that type of words. Well we'd got to learn those - afresh.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 It was about Army routine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Army routines, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Tactics and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, yes. That's right - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 It wasn't so much on general matters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 General - no, no. No. No. No. Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So really your school type education stopped?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 When I left the school. That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Do you have any regrets about your education at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, I don't have any regrets only I wish I'd have learnt more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes, definitely. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you attend any part time education afterwards, any evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
No, well you see what happened after that, when I left the Army and joined the dance business - we had - used to work in the afternoons, tea dances and work at nights 'til twelve o'clock, see - at the night
 dance. So we did - we had - we had two sessions a day seven days a week. So we hadn't much time for - oh no, no. Yes we used to - we used to love it. We used to love it. In fact - we done - at Nottingham Palais - we done exactly what they're doing this d
ays. The old can-can. We were doing that in 1926. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How much were you paid when you first went in the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh my money - first in the Army was - full wage was two shillings a week. But - if you - say you wore your boots out or wanted them men
ded, that all came out of that two shillings. You had to pay - we had to pay - exactly the same as what a full grown man had to pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 The Army provided your uniform?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, no. You bought it - they provided you with a first set. After that you paid 
for it. You paid twelve and six for your boots. You paid thirty-five shillings for a suit of khaki. I forget the price for your red tunic and helmet and whatnot. But - that all came out of your money. And you were - once you put down for anything - then y
o
u're in debt. And on one occasion - I went - to the pay parade and the first one to be called out was the colour sergeant. Of course he used to call out - and he said - myself - sixty shillings. Boy Goodchild - one penny, and don't come for another month.
 So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How did you get on for money then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well we used to have to clean some of them up - clean them up ready for church parade. That meant to say you got the - start with their boots, their tunic, their helmet, their card pouch, their belt and t
hen you finished up by cleaning their instrument for 'em. For the men. Yes, we used to - that's right, we used to work for the men. They used to give us tuppence to do that. And if anybody wanted a - urgent letter posted well the Post Office was a mile aw
ay, so we used to earn another penny by posting their letters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How about leave, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2182234\charrsid7304980 what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  sort of holidays with pay did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - my first leave was from Ireland. I joined the Army see and went to Aldershot. And then in October when the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 manoevers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
 came on, that's when all the regiments change round, change their stations. We went to - Mullingar in Ireland. And we had our Christmas leave which was six weeks - from there. But we had thirty- eight shillings to last us for six weeks. That included ou
r fares. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How did you get on then? What did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well we simply paid our fares. Paid our fares and then - attached ourselves to one member of the family. See. They knew our circumstances.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You went to one of your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes. Yes, I went to my second sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How about Saturdays and Sundays? This is before 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well - Saturdays and Sundays were - was always - Saturday afternoons, there was an old saying in the Army - in bed or out of barracks. See. Well of course us b
oys we were only too pleased to get out of barracks. So of course we - either football or cricket or whatever's going we used to do. Then Saturday nights we always make a beeline for the Hippodrome. The early doors. Hippodrome at Aldershot. Fourpence. And
 - we used to thoroughly enjoy it. That was the rest of our entertainment for the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How did you get on with other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 All right, I used to get on fine with everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 It was quite a happy atmosphere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How about the officers or the N.C.O's above you, how did you feel they treated you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10839993\charrsid7304980 Well the majority of them were very, very good. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Very good. I mean, they used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 use}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  - you usually find - that somebody who had just made lance corporal, ac
ting unpaid lance corporal, they used t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6964930\charrsid7304980 o think they were young generals.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
 And of course their authority, they used to use it. They used it far more than anybody higher up. Oh the officers were gentleman. They really were. Yes. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You liked the work did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes. Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Would you have preferred any other type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well - I didn't know any. I didn't know any other occupation apart from that you see. I mean, naturally being in a band in the Army all the time I wanted to be in the music line when I came out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you ever think while you were in the Army - did you ever feel you wished you were free to go in a jazz band or any orchestra?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well we used to run our own jazz band in our regiment. We were t
he first regiment to have a jazz band. Yes, one of the officers formed it. And of course me being the only saxophone player in the band I was - most essential. So - I went straight into - went straight from the Army into a - a dance band.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So you never really hankered after any other occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How long was the training period or apprenticeship before you were a full soldier; or full bandsman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - well - you see - the - a boy naturally you - we used to - nine o'clock
 was the practice time. From nine 'til twelve. That was for the full band. Under the band master. Then in the afternoons the boys used to go in again from two 'til four - practice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you feel that the officers and soldiers had the same interests, a 
lot of people in those days say there was a great division of interest between trained craftsmen and labourers, did you feel that or not? Quite often craftsmen wouldn't let labourers in the same trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well because, trade unionism we didn't und
erstand at all in those days. We knew nothing about it in the Army. There's no - there's nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 This was just something you didn't know about?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 We didn't understand at all. We never - we never got in touch with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 It was completely outside your doors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Absolutely outside our doors, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Would you say that full time work has changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well it's certainly broadened it. Oh yes, broadens your outlook on life. Oh no end.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
When you left the school and went into the Army, how much did it change your life, did you spend your weekends any differently, you now had two bob a week to spend instead of nothing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - all the weekends all we used to think about really was - sport. Sports. That's right, yes. Yes. Oh yes, we used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Could you tell me about how you spent your spare time when you were first in the Army, for example how did you go and meet girls and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh - oh well we had our own re
gimental coffee bar you see and grocery bar and the men had their canteen. Oh yes, but - we weren't allowed in their canteen. But as regards girls, oh girls were out of it. They were foreign to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 After you joined the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 After you joined the
 Army, as a boy. Yes. When you came in your service, become a man - then of course, you sent out and about more. But - oh - to be seen with a girl you - oh - wasn't done. It was all - it was sort of taboo. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did the other soldiers enforce this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes, yes, yes. Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What would they do if they saw a boy out with a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well it's all according to who it was that saw you, see. But - I don't think any of our boys - were interested in girls. No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 He had to wait 'til he was ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Eighteen, that's right - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 When he was considered a man by the Army?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, yes, yes. That's when your money went up from two bob to seven bob.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you make any new friends, any boys or girls, at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 In the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Outside your army pals, in Aldershot or wherever you happened to be stationed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well - it's all according to where you were stationed. I mean - during the '14 - '18 war you see we were shifted from - we came from Ireland back
 to England and we were stationed at Felixstowe. Well - I made quite a few friends at Felixstowe. Yes. So naturally, we boys - when Kitchener}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 s Army joined up - what we - what we done was - we went round all the old tunics and took the brass buttons off the tunics and sold 'em to Kitchener}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
s Army. They used to sew 'em on their blue - coats. So we made quite a lot of money like that. And perhaps we'd be promenading along the promenade down there and - the - holidaymakers who were still down there - say, oh w
ould you like a piece of cake, would you like a cup of tea Tommy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You were quite popular during the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes. Oh yes, down there, yes, oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Where did you used to go with these friends, what sort of leisure activities - did you go out walking or cycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well - one - one of the boys had a cycle and we all used to have a little go at it. But - there wasn't a - apart from sport, football and - whatnot - there wasn't a lot that we used to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What sort of things would you do in the evening if you weren't playing sport with the Army? Were there any cinemas or music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 We couldn't afford that. Oh no. We couldn't afford that. As I told you, fourpenny early }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 shows}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  at the Hippodrome was our -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was that the music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Yes - the Hippodrome at Aldershot, yes. And of course when we went to Ireland there wasn't any Hippodrome, we were - well away from the town. So of course we had - we had to make our won - perhaps we'd - might learn - a game of cards of some des
cription you see. All - all inside barracks. So you didn't get the chance to go out much. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 The Army absorbed you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Absolutely, yes. Full time. Yes, that's right. Right from the time you - from the time reveille went to lights out. That's righ
t, yes. Yes. Mind you, you always find plenty to do - cleaning your kit. And whatnot. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 When did you first take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - first time I think - was round about - about five years after leaving the Army. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What made you start taking an interest then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well one of the first things that - attracted our attention really was the general strike. 1926. And - I was playing then - I was playing down at - Margate or Cliftonville, at the Queens Highcliffe Hotel. Well 
we used to have the Monday off. So four of us - one of the boys had a car, he bought the wife and I and his own wife up to town to spend the night and we were going back first thing in the morning. But of course we got stranded out at Wembley. He was at -
 we were supposed to meet this fellow at London Bridge - at half past nine and we were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 stranded}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
 out at Wembley. So of course we had to hitchhike. We managed all right, just in time. And about ten minutes after we got away so they started turning the cars over. Etcetera. So we were very lucky - very lucky indeed to get out in time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So first being in the orphanage and then in the Army, this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 kept}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  you insulated from Trade unions as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes, yes, yes. Yes. Yes. That's right, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You didn't belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No - well we - I belonged to the musicians union. But that - that's - when I - yes, yes, yes, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did your mother die in childbirth or was there some other reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well it was just - apparently it wa
s just after childbirth. She'd had ten children and I was the last one. And soon after I was born - apparently - she died. And the shock of course sent my father }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 melancholy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 . And the children naturally were all put into an orphanage. That's how I become to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They seemed to split the family a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes. The two sisters were adopted by a couple.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So they didn't actually go into an orphanage?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They didn't - no, no, but the three boys went into the orphanage. The eldest brother went to Enfiel
d. And the second eldest and myself, we of course - we went to Brentwood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Do you know why they split your oldest brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No idea, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They didn't make much effort to keep the family together did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no. Oh no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Could you say exactly the age you went to Brentwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
I think it was - six years of age. I was six. Because I was put into the infants, what they call the infants in those days. That was - anybody under the age of seven. And when I became seven, then I
 was transferred to the main building with the big boys as we called 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What age did you leave Brentwood to go to Ongar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Twelve. Twelve or thirteen, I forget which, I don't - round about thirteen I think it was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You were probably about two years in Ongar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Could you tell us something of the day's routine at Brentwood, what was the system of getting you up, were there whistles or bells?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no, there was a - we had - we had a bugle. One of the boys in the 
band, he used to be detailed for that week, like the Army, and he blew reveille and of course - that woke everybody up. Then of course the officers as we called them, the men attendants, they used to go round to see that you were up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What time was this then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh - I suppose - varied I suppose - six o'clock. Six o'clock or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 half}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  past six. I know - in the winter we used to have just that little bit longer in bed. In the summer of course six o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What time did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Eight o'clock.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What happened between getting up and eight o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well of course you had to go and get washed and tidied up. Then of course you'd got to make your bed. See. And then when - once you'd - once - you were all clear in that line of cours
e you went downstairs to the day room, the big day room where all the boys used to collect and - wait for the breakfast call. Then when the - when the whistle went for breakfast we'd from up in our different companies, see, and march into the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So you were woken by a bugle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And the next command?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was a whistle. That's right, that's right, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 These companies you talk about, were they in a way actually like Army companies, did you have names for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well no, there was - they were in different ages. All the young boys in the first }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 squad}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
 and so on up to the elder boys, there were six - six squads. And - we used to have to - march into the dining room in our different squads always in the same rotation you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
You always went to meals with this squad that you belonged to? Did you do everything together, were you in the same classroom, did this squad }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 stick}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  together }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 throughout}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  the day more or less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes. Well yes, more or less. More 
or less. I mean, you used to form up with the squad, go into the breakfast, when you came out of course there was - you - you'd got your little job to do, whatever it was, help with the - clean the dormitories or whatever have you. And then of course you 
were fell in for school. And you marched in the different classrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What was the signal for falling }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2182234\charrsid7304980 out}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  - for school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh they used just a - a - either a whistle or - well - yes - a whistle mostly. That's right. Mostly whistle, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What was the six of a squad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Thirty or forty. Thirty or - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were these sub-divided in any way at all or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, no, no, they were all on a - all on a par.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was there any sort of monitorial system or prefects or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
No, not as regards with the - the boys. Just the officers were - they were - yes. Yes. And there was an officer more or less to each squad. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You said the discipline was quite severe, and yet in the instance you gave us the boys seemed to have merited this punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was there much sort of casual clipping round the ears or anything like this by the staff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - no, there was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7891465\charrsid7304980 only}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  one - one of the staff that used to do that sort of thing, and that was the - the - the
 one used to inspect the boys after they'd had their bath. You weren't allowed to get dressed until you'd passed his examination. And if you were - you went to hi- and he - rub his thumb down your back or round your thigh to see - and he caught - made dir
t, then he used to give you a sting across the bottom with a - a little strap he had, see. So that - that was the - he was about the only one, yes, yes. Otherwise if it was - anything serious then it was the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were your squad masters allowed to give the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, no, just the head one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 He was the only one allowed to cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, yes, he was the only one, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You said that one of them was a bit of a fanatic and made you chew each mouthful thirty times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes, yes, yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did he punish you if you didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Oh - well, yes. Oh yes, that would be - that's the reason he used to watch us. Used to watch us and if a boy was caught not chewing his - food the number of times that was issued out then of course he was punished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What sort of punishments were there other than the cane?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well - well it - used to find you some little job to do. Cleaning the toilets or something like that you see. Oh yes. That's right, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were there any other sort of rules like this, did any of the other staff have these sort of quirks, insist on certain things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
No, not exactly, but - if the - if you - if the whistle went and you didn't immediately stop and remain stationery, anybody caught running about after tha
t - then they were punished. You see. That's where the discipline came in, you were - the strict - it really was strict discipline. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 From the time you went there they really insisted that when the whistle goes you drop everything and you stand still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right. Yes. Yes. That's right, yes. Obedience. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And you also had to stop talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes. I mean, previous to the whistle going you - you - well - it was pandemonium. But directly that whistle went - could hear a pi
n drop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So in a way it was Army style discipline?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 It was. Yes. Yes. That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 The boys were sent out at quite a young age to different parts of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 
colonies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  and Empire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You said the boys would do anyt
hing to get out, and I asked you whether boys ever slipped out for a couple of hours in the evening and you said, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 no}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
, this wasn't possible?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No - because - the - the officers used to come round the dormitories until of course they knew that - everybod
y was - more or less - and then of course they had the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 night watchman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
 who also used to come - when the officers had finished coming round at ten o'clock the - periodically - every hour the night}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
watchman }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 used}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  to come round you see. So it would be very hard
 for - and besides there was - it was such a - it was in such an enclosed school that anybody wandering out in the grounds was spotted immediately. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did it have a wall round it or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 It - well - a hedge.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You could have got through without going out of the gate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - it would have been a bit of a - bit of a job. Oh yes, yes, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 But on the whole it was the supervision that kept you in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 It kept - oh yes, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You had age squads, was there very much activity between different age groups? Or were you more or less kept to your own age group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, in a - no, when - when you were in the playground everybody was mixed. You see. Everybody was mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They didn't keep the older boys separate from the younger ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no, no, no, no. One huge playground you see and every body was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Do you remember any children standing - out in your mind who were left out of things, sort of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7891465\charrsid7304980 lonely}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  children or perhaps slightly crippled children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
No. We never had any cripples. No. There was no cripple children among them. But if - if a boy was - a sort of bit backward or anything, well usually - one of the officers used to watch him and encourage somebody else to go and play wit
h him or try and entice him to do something you see. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They didn't let children get solitary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
No, no, no, no. You couldn't - you couldn't get solitary I mean because if you didn't enter into things then the other children used to take the mickey out of you. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So there was more or less social pressure on the children to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. In fact, later on - when - when you left the school you missed that you see, yes, you missed that. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You've obviously been interested in so many activities, do you think it's a result of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 Well - yes, well - I mean - then it - well when I'd left the school and went to the Army I was in - in everything. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Taking part in everything. Football, cricket, rugby or - hock
ey and everything else. Concert party and - then of course when I came out into civilian life again, the same thing happened again. Now I'm - booked up again.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You say you had one special chum at the school who became a bandmaster, when did you first 
pal up with him, was this in Brentwood or at Ongar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
At - Ongar. Yes, yes. You see, when we moved to Ongar - more or less the boys, that's when they were split up into four different blocks you see. And - and they all had their own cottage. I mean it 
was some cottage when you got fifty or sixty boys in it - some cottage. But still - that - they were confined to that cottage, see, now the band - had one big cottage. The carpenters had another, the gardeners had another and the plumber and painters had 
another. So - that's how they were split up and that's - this boy joined the band, that's when we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Do you remember any special friendships earlier on at Brentwood, or didn't they encourage boys to pal up, did they try and keep everyone active as a group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh no, you could pal up with any other boy, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Your brother would have been in a different age group, in a different squad from you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you get much chance to see him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well I saw - see him every day. Every
 spare time - if you weren't in school or you weren't doing anything at all we were all in the playground together. See, the brothers - and as - as I told you, remarkable at that - all these boys shouting their head off and whistling and whatnot and yet i
f I wanted my brother I simply shouted - my skissle. And he'd know. Or some other brother would shout for his and they could tell, above that noise they used to be able to tell their own brother's voice. Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You went on these supervised walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes. Honeypot Lane, yes, yes. Nature study walks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was that with an age group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well that was in your class from the school. See, that was from the schoolrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So you didn't get much chance to go outside the school with your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Oh no, no, no. No, you - you could - you never got any time at all outside the school with your brother. I mean outside the school itself. See.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Usually if you went outside the school it would be in a supervised age group?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right. That's right, yes. Yes, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Your sisters were married and started visiting you while you were at Ongar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Were you allowed to have visitors at Brentwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes. Yes, we had - that's right, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 At Ongar you had a housemother, was there any contact with women before this, were there any women on the staff at Brentwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Not in the boys - not in the boys side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So you didn't encounter a motherly ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 A new environment, yes. At - at Ongar you s
ee we had a - a foster mother and father And a - a lady help in the cottage. But although - they were there every boy had his own job to do so that the whole place was cleaned every day. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So you never had contact at all with women at Brentwood? How much did you see of your housemother at Ongar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh you saw her right from the word go, right from - early morning, breakfast and onwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was she something like a mother, could you go to her with personal worries or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes, and if - if she couldn't - or him - if the husband and wife couldn't attend to you they'd take you to the }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  - who was the head of the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 But did they create quite a homely atmosphere in these cottages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, yes. Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did you have any contact with the guardians of the place at Brentwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well - no, we never had any contact with them, they used to come - once a month and have their board meetings. But we - we might have seen them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 But they didn't interview the boys or anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, no, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did they at Ongar at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
No, the same applied at Ongar, they'd come and have their meeting and - unless there was something they wanted to see or do in the school you - we - well - we'd seldom see them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They'd perhaps have a tour of a workshop or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, yes, or - yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They might speak to the odd boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, that's it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 But you never were actually interviewed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
No, no, no. Well at Brentwood now and again they used to come round the shops, see, 'cos it used to make quite a tour for them. And - there was a quite a lot - quite a few shops to see too. As a school you know Brentwood was a marvellous place reall
y. A boy that wanted to take up a trade or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 On the whole would you say that you enjoyed your time at Brentwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well I enjoyed me time at Brentwood better than I did at Ongar. Yes. Yes. I suppose really that was because I had me brother
 with me. See, he left the school just before we went over to Ongar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 He didn't spend any time in Ongar with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What happened to him then, did he leave school early?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 He - he - no, he joined the Army. He went as a - as a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 band boy}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  he joined the Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 But you went from Brentwood to Ongar at thirteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Ongar. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And then you joined the Army at fifteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 How much older was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh Harry was - three or four years older, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Did he spend his two years in Ongar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
No, no. He went straight - from - from - from Brentwood he went straight into the - no, he must have been fourteen. Yes. Fourteen he must have gone into the Army then you see. That's right, yes, 'cos you could join the Army at fourteen as a }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 band boy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 . And that's - that's what he done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was there any particular reason why you took up music do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Well - I suppose it's because me brother done that - me brother joined the band you see and of course he encouraged 
me to join the band. And what we used to like was because the band used to go out on different little jobs. It was an outing for us, that's right, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 This was quite a highly prized thing was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh yes, oh yes. But - and the advantage too of being in the band was - that - you also had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7891465\charrsid7304980 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7891465\charrsid7304980  trade}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
. Another trade. You see, now I went into the shoemaker}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7891465\charrsid7304980 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
s shop apart from the band. So I spent part of the time in the shoemakers shop - part time band.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So if you didn't take up music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You just had the one - that's right, yes. That's right, yes, yes. Yes, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 On Sundays you used to go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And every evening or every night just before you went to bed you had your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 
squads}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  and said prayers all together, were you taught to say private prayers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well it was explained to us. But - we could kneel by our bedside and say our - a little prayer. Oh yes, that was explained to us. And quite a lot of the boys used to do it. Oh yes. Yes. Oh quite a common thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Did they use the prayer session to give you any sermons in particular, you told me for example that you never touched alcohol until you were ordered to drink a lot of rum while you were in the trenches?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right. Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was there any particular reason for this, were you warned against drink in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Oh yes, we used to - we had our - our own - temperance association. Quite a big class. Oh I still remember my lines as the past chief templar. I was one of the office
rs. Yes. So - and - oh - I used to have to say - we need also to learn how to spread abroad the principles of temperance and this to help the sorrowful and suffering throughout the world. I never forgot it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was there much temperance in the Army or were you fairly exceptional in that respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh there was quite a bit of temperance in the Army. Of course }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 band boys}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 , you weren't allowed to drink. You weren't allowed in the canteen. You could go in the coffee bar but not the canteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 But when you were out in the evening, up town or something, you could have gone in for a pint?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 If you were caught you were for it. Oh yes. Oh yes. Boys - seen going into a public house were - he was for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 What about when you'd finished your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 boys\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  service, did most of them start drinking then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well - yes, a good percentage of them. They used to think they were a man you see and of course that was that. Used to think that that was their job then to prove they were a man, go and drink a pint.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 So you think your early }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 adherence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  temperance more or less stemmed from Brentwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Yes, yes, oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was there any other sort of moral guidance or social guidance of this sort in the sermons, connected with religion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 Yes, there was quite a - quite a bit of - things were explained, like - all about religion and whatnot you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 And - every year there were so many - children picked out to be confirmed and all that. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 This was quite a busy part of the school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Oh defin
itely, yes, yes, we used to have the regular clergyman come from outside you see and take - take the services and - we used to have real good sermons and what not. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was there any sort of private }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 counsel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7891465\charrsid7304980 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 ing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  at all, they warned you against the 
evils of drink but did they warn you against the evils of women or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 No, not - no, no, no, sex wasn't mentioned there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They have sex education in schools these days don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 These days but then sex was never mentioned. Yes, I mean, well - well you wouldn't - at Ongar you see we had the chance of }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7891465\charrsid7304980 talking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980  to the girls but - never entered our head you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They didn't explain it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 They didn't - no, no, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You say you went back to visit the place once, how long after you'd left was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Well I came - when I came on leave from France. During the first world war, I came back and - there was an air raid on at the time that night. And a friend of mine, we went down there together to see the place. 
It was the night that John Bull's place got bombed. Now, well that was - they remember that anyway. Hit John Bull's place got bombed. Now, well that was - they remember that anyway. Hit John Bull's place. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 But - oh it was - oh it was very, very strange too.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 He was a boy who'd been at Brentwood with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 
Yes. Yes. Well - this - I got into - when we - when we turned up at the school of course the first thing they said to me was, ooh, you're dead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 Was this Brentwood or Ongar you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 O
ngar. Yes. And - I said, oh no. They'd got it mixed up with my brother. See. Brother Harry, he got killed and - they thought it was me. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10097725 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 You went back to see your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5537235\charrsid7304980 house parents}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5915702 DG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2898258\charrsid7304980 That's right, yes, yes, oh yes. Oh yes, it was quite a big occasion to go back and be one of the old scholars see. Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
